          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 3,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "supporting us on Patreon",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/cyber-shadow-switch-review/Patreon.com/switchaboo",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 3,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " so that we can continue to keep the website running and get our fortnightly podcast two days early.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Checkpoints allow you to spend your hard earned currency on restorations to health and SP as they won't occur automatically when you reach one. You can also purchase a fighter drone that will fight alongside you temporarily, which are great during boss fights. This then brings me to the game's Amiibo functionality (there's something I haven't said in quite a while). I only own the Shovel Knight Amiibo where you can call upon the titular knight to fight alongside you in lieu of the drone. It's a clever little nod but it doesn't help the game's case to make a name for itself.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "World / Level Design",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Some of these levels may appeal to those who are gluttons for punishment. Certain checkpoints seem ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "way",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " too far away from each other and when in between these bouts are instant death pits and flying projectiles which cause exorbitant knockback, it'll simply make the player remember how hard these 2D 8 bit games actually were. I consider myself a compitent gamer who isn't opposed to a bit of difficulty but due to the exceedingly long length between some checkpoints, the game felt arbitrarily stretched out when I found myself replaying the same frustrating segments ten times in a row.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/01/image-15.png",
        "width": 1280,
        "height": 720
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyber Shadow",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is by no means a Metroidvania and yet, it does borrow some backtracking elements. As you venture through the first few chapters, you'll notice strange blocks and odd placements of objects and will likely think to yourself, \"what am I supposed to do here?\". You'll grit your teeth and concede defeat, carrying on throughout the level until you realise that an upgrade further on allows you to go back and solve the puzzle. It's never a must so players who simply want to carry on with the story can disregard it but for completionists and those with burning curiosities, it's a satisfying accomplishment.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Story / Personality",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The plot presents many twists and turns that'll keep the player invested; however, I never felt that the dialogue was particularly engaging. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyber Shadow",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "'s choppy pacing and stale characters puts a dampener on its presentation which is arguably its primary selling point.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/01/image-16.png",
        "width": 1280,
        "height": 720
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With all that being said, the world that has been created within ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyber Shadow",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is something to admire. It captures the post-apocalyptic future/technologically advanced society motif wonderfully and simultaneously paints a drab yet bright picture of a civilisation gone awry.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Graphics / Art Direction",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Being published by Yacht Club Games, you can make graphical comparisons to the critically acclaimed ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Shovel Knight",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " within mere seconds of booting up ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyber Shadow",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". Some platforms and walls use identical assets but I wish to highlight how this is not, by any means, a bad thing. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Shovel Knight",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is praised for its modern recreation of the 8 bit aesthetic and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyber Shadow",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " expands on its foundations, seamlessly innovating on it with its neo sci-fi motif.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/01/image-17.png",
        "width": 1280,
        "height": 720
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyber Shadow ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "even goes so far as to implement optional CRT filters which provide waves of retro nostalgia. It's a neat little effect and while it may be heartwarming for those who grew up with leg warmers, mullets and Sony walkmans, nothing can beat the crisp HD visuals of modern screens.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Music / Sound Design",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Just like ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Shovel Knight",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", the chiptune soundtrack is heaven to one's ears. It brings forth even more nostalgic waves whilst making it its own with a darker undertone. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In regards to the sound effects, you can instantly tell that Yacht Club Games also had a hand in this department. The recognisable crashes, the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "shing",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " of weapons and the quick jingles that occur upon simple actions all scream ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Shovel Knight",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " and whilst it may not fit the game's tone at times, it still brings back fond memories, nonetheless.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 1,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Click here to read our review of Red Colony",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
